Issues.Body:
**What version of Tailwind CSS are you using?**

3.3.5

**What build tool (or framework if it abstracts the build tool) are you using?**

Playground

**Reproduction URL**

https://play.tailwindcss.com/bY5cpiQqrA?file=config

**Describe your issue**

I'm starting to create a series of dynamic utilities which set (and inherit/override) a series of custom properties, but very soon ran in to this bug¬†(unless there's something wrong with the way I'm specifying the custom property?)

With the following in my plugin...

```js
      matchUtilities(
        {
          fz: (value) => ({
            '--font-size': value,
            fontSize: 'var(--font-size)',
          }),
        },
        {
          values: {
            math: { '--font-size': 'math', fontSize: 'var(--font-size)' },
            inherit: { '--font-size': 'inherit', fontSize: 'var(--font-size)' },
            initial: { '--font-size': 'initial', fontSize: 'var(--font-size)' },
            unset: { '--font-size': 'unset', fontSize: 'var(--font-size)' },
            revert: { '--font-size': 'revert', fontSize: 'var(--font-size)' },
            'revert-layer': { '--font-size': 'revert-layer', fontSize: 'var(--font-size)' },
          },
        }
      )
```

... when I use the class `fz-initial` in my HTML, I get this CSS

```css
.fz-initial --font-size{
  --font-size: initial;
  font-size: var(--font-size)
}

.fz-initial{
  font-size: var(--font-size)
}
```
